RIYADH: The Arab coalition said on Sunday that 138 Houthis had been killed during air strikes on two districts near the central Yemeni city of Marib. The coalition added that 17 military vehicles had also been destroyed in the 29 strikes carried out on Juba and Al-Kasarah during the last 24 hours. Juba is some 50 km south of Marib, whilst Al-Kasarah is 30 km northwest of the city. The coalition has reported near-daily strikes over the past month against the Iran-backed Houthis.